{
  "texts": [
    "The lower the cost, the better the clustering.",
    "So, we use the cost as the penalty for Hyperopt to find the best hyperparameters.Dimensionality reduction and clustering are powerful techniques for analyzing and interpreting data.",
    "However, dimensionality reduction can lead to losing important information and selecting the appropriate dimensions can be challenging [64].",
    "Furthermore, when dealing with large datasets, the curse of dimensionality can make computations impractical.",
    "Clustering algorithms, on the other hand, can be sensitive to noise and outliers, and the choice of distance metric can have a significant impact on the results."
  ]
}